NOLOGIN(8)                   System Manager's Manual                  NOLOGIN(8)

NAME
     nologin â€“ politely refuse a login

SYNOPSIS
     nologin

DESCRIPTION
     The nologin utility displays a message that an account is not available and
     exits non-zero.  It is intended as a replacement shell field for accounts
     that have been disabled.

     To disable all logins, investigate nologin(5).

SEE ALSO
     login(1), nologin(5)

HISTORY
     The nologin utility appeared in 4.4BSD.

